# claude-code-rlm — Marathon COMPLETE

All five phases of the `claude-code-rlm` `UserPromptSubmit` hook are implemented,
tested, committed, and pushed. `node --test test/unit.test.mjs` is green.

## What was built

A `UserPromptSubmit` hook (`rlm-hook.mjs`, dependency-light Node ESM) that
dispatches Haiku to pre-explore the codebase before the main model's turn,
injecting findings as `<rlm_preresearch>` / `<rlm_analysis>` context.

- **Phase 1 — Core Hook (COMPLETE).** Subprocess-based Haiku invocation
  (fast / detailed / agentic modes), prompt assembly, SHA-256 cache,
  conversation-context gathering, skip heuristics, safe-by-default output
  formatting. Every failure path swallowed so the hook never blocks the user.

- **Phase 2 — SDK-Direct Mode (COMPLETE).** `@anthropic-ai/sdk` added as a
  dependency. `RLM_USE_SDK=true` + `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` selects the SDK path;
  otherwise the subprocess behavior is unchanged. `callHaikuFastSDK`,
  `callHaikuDetailedSDK`, and `callHaikuAgenticSDK` (tool-use loop dispatching
  Glob/Grep/Read/Write/Bash(git:*), capped at `RLM_MAX_TURNS`, default 10).
  SDK errors fall back gracefully.

- **Phase 3 — Semantic Caching (COMPLETE).** `embedText` → `Float32Array`,
  pure `cosineSimilarity`, `.embedding` float32 sidecars, `semanticLookup`
  on SHA miss (threshold `RLM_SEMANTIC_THRESHOLD`, default 0.92), and an
  `index.json` reverse index (inline vectors, single-read lookup) that
  self-heals from the `.embedding` files as source of truth. Gated on
  `RLM_SEMANTIC_CACHE=true` — zero extra I/O when off.

- **Phase 4 — Conversation Context Awareness (COMPLETE).**
  `extractPriorRLMBlocks` / `extractPriorBlocksFromTranscript` recover prior
  pre-research blocks from the transcript JSONL; `classifyIntentLocal` +
  `intentsOverlap` + `findReusablePriorBlockWithMtime` decide reuse;
  `computeChangedFiles` (mtime, per-block `ts` window) gates it. On a hit,
  `main()` emits a lightly-marked continuation block and skips Haiku entirely.
  `RLM_CONTEXT_WINDOW` (default 5) bounds the look-back. Transparent — always on.

- **Phase 5 — Metrics Dashboard (COMPLETE).** `appendMetric` writes one JSON
  line per invocation at every `main()` exit (event, latency_ms, mode,
  input_len, cache_hit + extras), best-effort, never altering exit behavior.
  `bench/parse-log.mjs` aggregates per-UTC-day stats (hit/skip/error rates,
  nearest-rank p50/p95/p99 latency). `bench/dashboard.mjs` renders a
  standalone, XSS-safe static HTML dashboard (`renderHTML`) and serves it on
  port 9876 with `--serve` (re-aggregates the live log per request).

## Tests

- **272 unit tests green** (`node --test test/unit.test.mjs`), 26 groups.
  Phase-5 coverage: Group 24 (metrics log append), Group 25 (JSONL parsing +
  aggregation math, direct import of parse-log.mjs), Group 26 (HTML render +
  escaping, direct import of dashboard.mjs).
- **15 integration tests green** (`RUN_INTEGRATION_TESTS=1 node --test
  test/integration.test.mjs`) — unaffected by parse-log/dashboard (off the
  hook path).
- Unit tests inline faithful copies of hook logic rather than importing
  `rlm-hook.mjs` (which calls `main()` on load); the standalone bench modules
  guard their CLI behind `import.meta.url === pathToFileURL(argv[1]).href`, so
  they ARE imported directly.

## Remaining open questions (from docs/plan/plan.md §160 — deferred, not blocking)

1. **Max turns in agentic mode** — 10 is a guess; needs empirical testing on
   large codebases.
2. **Scratch file location** — Phase 2 writes to a pid-scoped scratch path to
   avoid the `.claude/rlm-scratch.md` collision called out in the plan.
3. **Multi-project sessions** — cache is not yet re-keyed/invalidated when
   `cwd` changes between turns.
4. **Cost tracking** — per-run Haiku token usage (~2K–10K in / ~500–2K out
   estimated) not yet measured; the Phase-5 metrics log is the foundation for it.
5. **Race conditions** — concurrent hook invocations do last-writer-wins cache
   writes; no lock file yet (accepted per plan).
